JOHANNESBURG - Consumers will know on Thursday afternoon whether interest rates will stay the same. The Reserve Bank s Monetary Policy Committee has been locked in meetings since Tuesday, deliberating on the country s next policy stance.Inflation has slowed to 5.3 percent, leaving some analysts with hope that the rate will not change.READ: Interest rate cut unlikely amid risks to currencyBut the country hasn t been without challenges.South Africa suffered a double downgrade in April, and the Central Bank is expected to take this into consideration.The MPC is also expected to share its view on the country s growth prospects.eNCA